title.85: Adventures on the Planet of the Apes (1975) #11

description.2: The Golem strikes! But will his prey be the Nazis...or the captive Invaders?!
description.4: The doctored photo is wreaking havoc on Howard's Presidential campaign and forces him and Beverly to hit the road again. But they have bigger issues at hand when they find themselves being targeted by assassins!
description.6: Following an explosion from his enervator device, Dr. Curt Connors finds his control over the Lizard to wane. Spider-Man uncovers Stegron in a covert laboratory, but is quickly disoriented by the arrival of S.H.I.E.L.D. agents. Will Spider-Man, and the Lizard, be able to stop Stegron before he takes the life of Curt Connor's son?
description.7: The Vision attempts a negotiation with Doom to release the Avengers from Attuma's mind control. Meanwhile, Attuma encounters a sneak attack from the Sub-Mariner and Wonder Man!
description.8: Captain America and the Falcon are trapped in the domain of the Swine!
description.9: Hawkeye and Two-Gun Kid guest-star! The Champions encounter some strange goings-on in the Arizona desert. The shadowy Warlord Kaa has been possessing local ranchers...and the Champions are next!
description.13: Watch out, Garden State! In a confrontation with Bullseye, Daredevil is strapped to a giant arrow and shot headlong towards New Jersey!
description.14: Captain Marvel's duel with the Kree Sentry rages on! And if that wasn't enough to deal with, he'll have to survive the claws of THE CHEETAH!
description.17: Captain Marvel and Adam Warlock aid the Avengers in their fight against Thanos. The fate of the universe hangs in the balance as the heroes race to destroy Thanos' artificial Soul Gem.
description.23: Kingpin has the wall-crawler pinned to a wall after his plan to resurrect Richard Fisk comes to fruition. Will Spidey be able to talk sense into Kingpin before he makes an irrevocable mistake? And what cost will Spider-Man have to pay to bring Kingpin's son back to life? A shocking conclusion that will forever change Marvel's most maligned villain!
description.24: Still in the clutches of Attuma, the Avengers must fend off attacks from Dr. Doom, Namorita, and the Amphibians of the Hydrobase! With villains this strange, expect a stranger battle!
description.25: Agron has broken loose! It's up to Captain America and Falcon to contain his dangerous energy-form to save the day!
description.26: The Champions' battle with the Russians converges in one show stopping conclusion! Plus, Ivan's tragic past is laid out in full...and a new member joins the team!
description.28: The First Marvel work of superstar artist John Romita Jr.!  Spidey takes the silver screen! Desperate for cash after posting Aunt May’s bail, Peter accepts a starring role on the set of “Spawn of the Spider.” But is the Hollywood salary worth it? Plus, Peter’s night out with Mary Jane turns into a run-in with criminals in “Chaos at the Coffee Bean”!
description.30: Captain America vs. the mutant radical, Magneto!
description.35: Howard just can't seem to avoid upsetting the wrong people. On his Presidential campaign, his enemies seem to have him up against the wall when a provocative picture of him and Beverly surfaces!
description.36: Howard the Duck is the ultimate hero in his first annual issue! Howard must save his roommates and friends from an evil plot by Roxxon Oil. Set in the mystical world of Arabia, this comic is chock full of genies, magic carpets, sultans...and thieves!
description.37: Deviant scientist Zakka has harnessed a way to revive old villains of the past for his present-day schemes! It's up to Thena, Karkas and Ransak to battle Jack the Ripper, Attila the Hun's army, and more before facing their final challenge...
description.40: Adapting James Fenimore Cooper's classic, "The Last of the Mohicans."
description.41: The S.H.I.E.L.D. research team find themselves as the captives of the Celestials in the Andes Mountains! Can they actually make the escape from the City of the Gods? Not without the fight of their lives, they won't!
description.42: Hulk says his final goodbye to Jarella. Will this tragedy spiral the Green Goliath out of control?
description.43: It's a blowout blockbuster action issue! Cap takes on Agent Axis! The Human Torch fights Hyena! And Sub-Mariner battles it out with Shark!
description.44: It's a battle to the death between the cunning cutlass of Commander Kraken and the peerless power of Iron Man! Can Shell Head manage to pull a fast one over Kraken's head and save his friends before they're buried at sea?
description.46: James-Michael - trapped and alone! Without Amber and Omega being there to protect him, James-Michael must rely on his mysterious omega powers to survive against the Wrench...
description.47: On his quest to find Odin, Thor will have to fight his way through the Stone Men of Saturn!
description.48: HIM has arrived...and he's looking for Dracula! The man who would become Adam Warlock is after the Lord of the Vampires!
description.49: The Thing, trapped in the Negative Zone! And after meeting Reed Richards of Counter-Earth, Ben's hope for escape looks ever bleaker.
description.60: Fresh out of the big house, Gladiator and the Beetle attack Daredevil with murderous vengeance. But the Man Without Fear’s been waiting for them…
description.61: You would think Spider-Man and a man named Tarantula would get along because of their arachnid similarities. Unfortunately…the Tarantula becomes one of Spidey's deadliest foes!
description.68: The Defenders take on the Blue Bullet! Plus, Jacqueline Falsworth undergoes a transformation...
description.70: Howard and Beverly find themselves in dessert danger when the deadly Ginger Bread Man comes a-calling!
description.72: Doctor Strange sojourns to Phaseworld, where he becomes entrapped in a demonic love triangle! Clea's life hangs in the balance.
description.73: Spider-Man vs. the Kingpin! After recovering from a catatonic state, Kingpin finds himself back in villainous form. Peter receives a surprise gift of furniture from his closest friends, but before he can relish the moment, he must consider where things stand with MJ. Will Peter be able to be honest with himself...and the girl he loves?
description.74: A visit from Triton of the Inhumans! But is Triton really who he claims to be? The Scarlet Witch uses hex powers to find out. After the Vision disposes of the Serpent Crown in the Pacific Ocean, he is attacked by annoyed Atlantean warriors!
description.75: While trying to restore Falcon's memories, Cap crosses paths with a beastly humanoid known as Agron. How can Captain America take down a "man" who grows stronger and larger with each step?
description.76: Ivan Petrovich has spent his life as a father and protector to Black Widow. Will Ivan be reunited with Natasha once more? Meanwhile, Hercules, Angel and Ghost Rider are subdued by the Russians...and Crimson Dynamo unveils a shocking secret!
description.86: The Gladiator takes on Ghost Rider, following the orders of his boss the Enforcer!
description.87: Thena and Kro announce a...truce? While the Eternals and Deviants on earth participate in an educational press conference, a S.H.I.E.L.D. research team vanishes just outside of the City of the Space Gods. Coincidence? Don't bet on it!
description.88: The Hulk is in dire need of Doctor Strange's mystical expertise. But all does not go as planned when Ol' Greenskin arrives in Manhattan- will Jarella find salvation?
description.89: After a near fatal accident during a routine flight from Stark Satellite One, Tony Stark is ends up stranded on a ship called the Northern Light. But when his friends Abe and Krissy decided to lead a search party they instead end up being taken captive by Commander Kraken! Will Tony be able to save his friends and defeat the mad pirate!
description.91: Re-presenting the origin of Donald Blake! (originally featured in Thor #159)
description.92: Blade the Vampire Hunter hunts Dracula! But will the Lord of the Vampires be able to turn Blade as this thrall?
description.93: The X-Men's trip to Cassidy Keep has been interrupted by an attack from Black Tom and the Juggernaut, who seek to kill the group of mutants.
description.94: The Frightful Four are hiring! Who will become the latest member of this nefarious crew? The answer will shock you!

0.text: The Thing and Black Goliath team up for a face off with the Hijacker!

3.text: The Defenders split up to look for the missing Doctor Strange!

5.text: Daimon Hellstrom - defeated! Satan - supreme at last! But nothing is as it seems, as the Lord of Darkness will soon find out in this holiday special!

10.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

11.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

12.text: A galactic adventure guest-starring the Inhumans!

13.text: Watch out, Garden State! In a confrontation with Bullseye, Daredevil is strapped to a giant arrow and shot headlong towards New Jersey!

14.text: Captain Marvel's duel with the Kree Sentry rages on! And if that wasn't enough to deal with, he'll have to survive the claws of THE CHEETAH!

15.text: Nova must face down Tyrannus and his colossal Earth-Shaker robot! Even more frightening, Nova comes face-to-face with Stan Lee!

16.text: Marvel legend Jack Kirby presents Black Panther in his first ongoing series! While helping Abner Little recollect a precious artifact, Black Panther runs afoul of the Collectors! And in the midst of the tussle…an ancient time machine is activated! Enter Hatch-22, a creature from a time and space unknown.

18.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

19.text: Shang-Chi's everlasting fight against his father Fu Manchu continues in "The Bridge of a Thousand Dooms!"

20.text: Crossover alert! Iron Man blasts his way into Jack Russell’s path! And just in time -- the Masked Marauder has come into possession of some dangerous tech!

22.text: Following last issue’s shocking revelation about Big Brother, Luke Cage must prove himself against the criminal hotshot! But what does a medieval-themed carnival have to do with all this?

27.text: From the same cocoon that birthed Adam Warlock, Paragon is born, with the help of Doctor Strange!

28.text: Spidey takes the silver screen! Desperate for cash after posting Aunt May’s bail, Peter accepts a starring role on the set of “Spawn of the Spider.” But is the Hollywood salary worth it? Plus, Peter’s night out with Mary Jane turns into a run-in with criminals in “Chaos at the Coffee Bean”!

31.text: Thing and Thor's clash with Seth continues! But the wily god of death has another trick up his sleeve - a being known only as the DEVOURER!

32.text: NIGHTMARE IN NEW MEXICO! Spider-Man along with Banshee find themselves in the secret town of Liberty, New Mexico to cover the impending fight between Hulk and Woodgod. Spider-Man's demand for answers suddenly gets him caught in between the battle. Will he come out unscathed? The story continues in the next issue…

34.text: Nighthawk must convince the Hulk to carry Cobalt Man into New York Harbor to minimize the threat of Cobalt Man’s explosion!

39.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

45.text: Carol Danvers takes flight as the Kree-empowered Ms. Marvel!

50.text: Who wouldn't want to see Spider-Man battle an enemy in the world famous Central Park? Spidey must defeat Kraven the Hunter, a man of extreme physical prowess. Oh, and he has to face a few live, hungry tigers too.

54.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

55.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

56.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

58.text: The Avengers are under the collar of Attuma, and their first mission is the elimination of Namor! Will the underwater monarch go on the lam from Earth’s Mightiest Heroes? Not a chance! Namor challenges Attuma head-on, while Doctor Doom exploits Iron Man’s fatal flaw.

59.text: Doctor Strange vs. Xander the Merciless! Clea loses control over her mystical abilities.

60.text: Fresh out of the big house, Gladiator and the Beetle attack Daredevil with murderous vengeance. But the Man Without Fear’s been waiting for them…

61.text: You would think Spider-Man and a man named Tarantula would get along because of their arachnid similarities. Unfortunately…the Tarantula becomes one of Spidey's deadliest foes!

62.text: Iron Fist is on the lam after the Golden Tigers frame him for the murder of costumed hero William Hao. Misty Knight and Colleen Wing know the truth about Iron Fist, and will stop at nothing to help their friend and ally out of this sticky jam! Iron Fist vs. Chaka!

63.text: Thor has fallen under the mental domination of the Corruptor! Can the Human Rocket withstand the power of a thunder god?

64.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

65.text: Clash of the gods! Ben Grimm's partner in crime fighting is none other than the MIGHTY THOR! But even these two powerhouses may be outmatched against the Egyptian god Seth, and his armies of the dead!

66.text: A demonic creature comes to Earth and wreaks havoc in the city. Steve Rogers, AKA Captain America, plus a collection of allies, must figure out what to do next.

67.text: Featuring Marvel's most daring super-spy, Nick Fury! Learn at long last Fury's ultimate secret: how does he survive near-fatal injuries, and stay young even after serving in World War II?

69.text: While meeting at Doctor Strange’s Sanctum Sanctorum, the Defenders are attacked by Egghead's Emissaries of Evil!

71.text: In the Court of Anubis, Mindstar reveals that he is actually Daimon's real estate agent, Silas Warden!

72.text: Doctor Strange sojourns to Phaseworld, where he becomes entrapped in a demonic love triangle! Clea's life hangs in the balance.

77.text: The fists of fury fly as White Tiger, Iron Fist, Shang-Chi, and Jack of Hearts take on the menace of the ‘Corporation’! Misty Knight guest-stars!

78.text: The Inhumans unite against demon foes in a deadly battle!

79.text: War in an Arctic wasteland! Shang-Chi alone can defeat the forces of his father Fu Manchu.

82.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

83.text: No, that’s not Sandman drowning Power Man in quicksand…it’s the all-new Chemistro! The mysterious Big Brother turns out to be the one deploying Arch Morton – so Cage takes the fight directly to Big Brother’s stronghold…

84.text: Silver Surfer pits his power cosmic against the Guardians of the Galaxy's greatest foes--the Badoon!

85.text: As the ape army invades the mutant city, Taylor, Brent and Nova desperately try to survive. This is it, this is the issue where everything comes to an explosive end! Do not miss the epic fate of the Planet of the Apes!

96.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

97.text: Nighthawk and Doc Strange pack their bags for Nevada…to perform an exorcism! Kyle suspects that his oldest friend, Patricia ‘Trish’ Starr, is possessed by demons. Enter Shazana and her monstrous hordes, here to claim our dimension!

98.text: Iron Fist finds a (very) worthy opponent in the Golden Tigers Gang. Leader Chaka shows his true colors, and swears to topple Ward Meachum. But why? Iron Fist accused of murder!
